 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5285/cloningduplicating-a-workspace-for-presentation-possible/?answer=5289#post-id-5289</link><description>Can you clone a display? Yes. Can you clone a workspace? No. You changed from one term to the other between the first and last paragraphs, so I can't tell which you're actually interested in knowing about.

Workspaces are unique and can only be drawn to one display at a time. No window manager on any operating system allows the content of a single workspace/virtual desktop/tag/whatever to be displayed on multiple distinct displays. You *can* clone displays using RandR, however, but not dynamically. You'd need to write a script or some such to switch the display properties when needed.</description><pubDate>Thu, 01 Jan 2015 23:41:22 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5285/cloningduplicating-a-workspace-for-presentation-possible/?answer=5289#post-id-5289</guid></item><item><title>Comment by saljut7 for &lt;p&gt;Can you clone a display? Yes. Can you clone a workspace? No. You changed from one term to the other between the first and last paragraphs, so I can't tell which you're actually interested in knowing about.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Workspaces are unique and can only be drawn to one display at a time. No window manager on any operating system allows the content of a single workspace/virtual desktop/tag/whatever to be displayed on multiple distinct displays. You &lt;em&gt;can&lt;/em&gt; clone displays using RandR, however, but not dynamically. You'd need to write a script or some such to switch the display properties when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5285/cloningduplicating-a-workspace-for-presentation-possible/?comment=5294#comment-5294</link><description>"No window manager on any operating system allows the content of a single workspace/virtual desktop/tag/whatever to be displayed on multiple distinct displays." -&gt;This is what I wanted to know.  I have to switch my display settings from "expand" to "clone" everytime I want the 1st or the 2nd.THXALOT</description><pubDate>Sat, 03 Jan 2015 00:59:08 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/5285/cloningduplicating-a-workspace-for-presentation-possible/?comment=5294#comment-5294</guid></item></channel></rss>